object.script:
si=math.sin co=math.cos pi=math.pi pi2=pi*2 BRT = 200
function onTick() zoom = input.getNumber(3) mapX = input.getNumber(1) mapY = input.getNumber(2) GREY = input.getBool(1) TR = property.getNumber("TextR") TG = property.getNumber("TextG") TB = property.getNumber("TextB") compass=input.getNumber(4)*pi2*-1 BR = property.getNumber("BackroundR") BG = property.getNumber("BackroundG") BB = property.getNumber("BackroundB") BRT = input.getNumber(5) end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() -- Get the screen's width and height h = screen.getHeight() CPX, CPY = map.mapToScreen(mapX, mapY, zoom, w, h, mapX, mapY)
screen.setMapColorOcean(BR, BG, BB) screen.setMapColorShallows(BR-5, BG-5, BB-5) screen.setMapColorLand(BR-10, BG-10, BB-10) screen.setMapColorGrass(BR-15, BG-15, BB-15) screen.setMapColorSand(BR-20, BG-20, BB-20) screen.setMapColorSnow(BR-25, BG-25, BB-25)
screen.drawMap(mapX, mapY, zoom)
screen.setColor(0, 0, 0, BRT) drawPointer(CPX,CPY,10,compass)
screen.setColor(5, 5, 5) screen.drawRectF(0, 0, w, 2) screen.drawRectF(0, 0, 2, h) screen.drawRectF(0, h-2, w, 2) screen.drawRectF(w-2, 0, 2, h)
end function drawPointer(x,y,s,r,...) a=... a=(a or 30)*pi/360 x=x+s/2*si(r) y=y-s/2*co(r)
screen.drawTriangleF(x,y,x-s*si(r+a),y+s*co(r+a),x-s*si(r-a),y+s*co(r-a)) end

-- Tick function that will be executed every logic tick function onTick() value = input.getNumber(1) -- Read the first number from the script's composite input output.setNumber(1, value * 10) -- Write a number to the script's composite output end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() -- Get the screen's width and height h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) -- Set draw color to green end

t = {} t_time = {} max_time = 200 r = 28 zoom = 1 cX = 0 cY = 0 indicator_range = 500 function onTick()
tbool = {} tbool[0] = input.getBool(1) tbool[1] = input.getBool(2) tbool[2] = input.getBool(3) tbool[3] = input.getBool(4) tbool[4] = input.getBool(5) tbool[5] = input.getBool(6) tbool[6] = input.getBool(7)
zoom_in = input.getBool(9) zoom_out = input.getBool(10)
if zoom_in and zoom > 0.2 then zoom = zoom - 0.001 end if zoom_out and zoom < 1 then zoom = zoom + 0.001 end
range = input.getNumber(30) display_range = range * zoom
angle_pos = input.getNumber(29) - 1.5
if (angle_pos <= 0.1) then for k in pairs(t) do t[k] = nil end end
for i=0, 6 do if tbool[i] then t_dist = input.getNumber(i*4 + 1) t_angle = angle_pos if (t_dist > 15) then t[t_dist] = t_angle t_time[t_dist] = 0 end end end
t_dist = input.getNumber(1) t_angle = input.getNumber(2)
end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() -- Get the screen's width and height h = screen.getHeight() cX = w/2 +15 cY = h/2 screen.setColor(20, 30, 20) j = math.floor(display_range/indicator_range) for i=1, j do ir = indicator_range*i/display_range *r screen.drawCircle(cX, cY, ir) end screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawCircle(cX, cY, r) posX = cX + r * math.cos(angle_pos) posY = cY + r * math.sin(angle_pos) posX2 = cX + r * math.cos(angle_pos-0.1) posY2 = cY + r * math.sin(angle_pos-0.1) posX3 = cX + r * math.cos(angle_pos-0.2) posY3 = cY + r * math.sin(angle_pos-0.2) posX4 = cX + r * math.cos(angle_pos-0.3) posY4 = cY + r * math.sin(angle_pos-0.3) screen.drawLine(cX ,cY, posX, posY) screen.setColor(0, 255, 0, 50) screen.drawTriangleF(cX, cY, posX, posY, posX4, posY4) screen.drawTriangleF(cX, cY, posX, posY, posX3, posY3) screen.drawTriangleF(cX, cY, posX, posY, posX2, posY2) screen.setColor(255, 0, 0)
for td, ta in pairs(t) do if (td > display_range) then td = display_range end tr = td/display_range * r tX = cX + tr * math.cos(ta) tY = cY + tr * math.sin(ta) alpha = (max_time - t_time[td])/max_time * 255 screen.setColor(255, 0, 0, alpha) screen.drawCircleF(tX, tY, 2) t_time[td] = t_time[td] + 1 if t_time[td] > max_time then t_time[td] = nil t[td] = nil end end
screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawText(5,5, "Range:") screen.drawText(5,12, display_range) screen.drawText(5,19, "Zoom:") screen.drawText(5,26, zoom) end

tX = {} tY = {} tD = {} arrLen = 20 i = 1 function onTick() t = input.getBool(1) t_dist = input.getNumber(1) t_angleX = input.getNumber(2) t_angleY = input.getNumber(3)
hdg = input.getNumber(5) zoom = input.getNumber(6) if zoom < 0 then zoom = 0 end
if (hdg < 0) then hdg = -hdg * 360 elseif (hdg > 0) then hdg = (1-hdg) * 360 end hdg = math.floor(hdg) hdg = string.format("%03d", hdg)
tX[i] = t_angleX tY[i] = t_angleY tD[i] = t_dist i = i+1 if i > arrLen then i = 1 end
tXsum = 0 tXnum = 0 for i, v in pairs(tX) do tXsum = tXsum + v tXnum = tXnum + 1 end angleX = tXsum/tXnum
tYsum = 0 tYnum = 0 for i, v in pairs(tY) do tYsum = tYsum + v tYnum = tYnum + 1 end angleY = tYsum/tYnum
tDsum = 0 tDnum = 0 for i, v in pairs(tD) do tDsum = tDsum + v tDnum = tDnum + 1 end dist = tDsum/tDnum
end
-- Draw function that will be executed when this script renders to a screen function onDraw() w = screen.getWidth() h = screen.getHeight() screen.setColor(0, 0, 0, 230) screen.drawRectF(w/2 - 9, 2, 17, 8) screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawText(w/2-7, 3,hdg) screen.drawRect(w/2 - 9, 1, 17, 8) screen.drawLine(0,5, w/2-9, 5) screen.drawLine(w/2+8,5,w,5) screen.setColor(0, 0, 0, 230) screen.drawRectF(0,h-9,w,11) screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawLine(0,h-10, w, h-10)
if t then screen.setColor(0, 255, 0) screen.drawText(5,h-7,"Distance: " ..tostring(math.floor(dist)))
rect_size = 15 * zoom if (rect_size < 2) then rect_size = 2 end aglX = round(angleX, 4) * 1000 * zoom aglY = round(angleY, 4) * 1000 * zoom x = w/2 - rect_size + aglX y = h/2 - rect_size - aglY screen.drawRect(x, y, rect_size *2, rect_size * 2) else screen.setColor(255, 0, 0) screen.drawText(5,h-7,"No Target") end end
function round(num, numDecimalPlaces) local mult = 10^(numDecimalPlaces or 0) return math.floor(num * mult + 0.5) / mult end
